I"f	<p>One major problem users face with Jekyll blog is adding new posts. While writing a new post using markdown language, to add a new image or formatting the blog post could be difficult.</p>

<p>Admin dashboard was one standout feature for wordpress which made life simple. Especially the bloggers who migrate from wordpress to jekyll find this as a disadvanatge.</p>

<p>But there is an option to add an admin dashboard to your jekyll blog.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Open Jekyll directory</li>
  <li>
    <p>Open  config.yml file in any text editor and add the below command under plugins and save it.</p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> `- jekyll-admin`
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p><img src="/assets/images/post/jekyll-admin-1.png" alt="" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Open ‘GemFile’ in any text editor and add the below command under ‘group :jekyll_plugins do’.</p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>     `gem "jekyll-admin"`
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p><img src="/assets/images/post/jekyll-admin-2.png" alt="" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Open command prompt and navigate to your jekyll blog directory and execute the below command.</p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> `bundle exec jekyll serve`
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p><img src="/assets/images/post/jekyll-admin-3.png" alt="" /></p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> Now this will deploy your blog in localhost.
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Open any webbrowser and naviagte to http://localhost:4000/admin or http://127.0.0.1:4000/admin to view the admin dashboard.</p>

    <p><img src="/assets/images/post/jekyll-admin-4.png" alt="" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Click on Posts in left sidebar to create a new post. Input all the necessary details and click on create.</p>

    <p><img src="/assets/images/post/jekyll-admin-5.png" alt="" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Now navigate to http://localhost:4000/ or http://127.0.0.1:4000 to view your blog and the post you have created will be visible in the blog.</p>

    <p><img src="/assets/images/post/jekyll-admin-7.png" alt="" /></p>
  </li>
</ol>
:ET